      "content": "Human-skin fibroblast NB1RGB cells form swirling patterns whose orientation differs when cultured on uncoated versus collagen type-I-coated dishes. Analysis shows that fibroblasts on uncoated dishes form larger patches of similarly oriented cells, while orientation correlations decay more quickly on collagen-coated dishes. This pattern difference is consistent across multiple experiments and dish materials."
